      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Wash the peaches thoroughly under cool running water, then cut them in half and remove the pits. Slice them into wedges.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "In a large salad bowl, combine the sliced peaches, halved mozzarella balls, and arugula or mixed greens.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add the toasted walnuts, crumbled feta cheese, and torn basil leaves to the bowl.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Drizzle the balsamic glaze over the salad mixture and season with salt and pepper to taste.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Gently toss the salad to combine all ingredients without mashing the peaches or mozzarella.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Chill the salad in the refrigerator for about 10-15 minutes before serving to allow flavors to meld.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Serve the salad on individual plates or directly from the bowl.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Spin leaves dry first. Whisk dressing ingredients until thick and pourable. Dress at the table, not in the kitchen, so it stays evenly coated.",
              "cause": "Dressing not emulsified, or salad too wet.",
              "symptom": "Dressing pools at the bottom of the bowl"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Combine everything cold and dress just before serving. Sturdy leaves (kale, chicory, romaine) cope with sitting; spinach and rocket don't.",
              "cause": "Dressed too early, or fruit/cheese added warm.",
              "symptom": "Leaves wilted by the time it reached the table"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Three parts oil to one part acid is the classic ratio. Adjust with a squeeze of lemon if it's flat, or a splash more oil if it's sharp.",
              "cause": "Wrong oil-to-acid ratio in the dressing.",
              "symptom": "Salad tastes too oily"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Toss the leaves with dressing first, then scatter cheese, nuts, croutons on top. Don't toss again after garnishing.",
              "cause": "Heavy ingredients added before tossing.",
              "symptom": "Toppings ended up in the bottom"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add-protein: top with grilled chicken, halloumi, or a soft-boiled egg for a main-course salad.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Crunch upgrade: scatter toasted nuts or seeds on top, pumpkin, almond, sunflower.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
